race.comment: VORIAH (12) has been in good form on the picnic circuit recently, and won't find this much harder. She drops 9kg from her last run, and with the aid of the pole position, she should be right in the finish again. PURE RAIN (9) left her run too late when finishing fifth as the favourite at Horsham just over 3 weeks ago. The blinkers going on for the first time will ensure that she does not get as far back here, and she can make amends. Follow your money. CROATIAN ART (1) won a couple of races last prep by leading all the way, including her last run at Tatura in the spring. She has won fresh up in the past, and with the aid of a 2kg claim, she could take some pegging back again. LADY MAESTRO (5) will be peaking third up and ready to show some good form again, and MISS REMSKI (6) had an excuse last start when getting pushed back along the rails. Include both in all combinations.
